pageContext.claim: “That story was a massive story [referring to the death of Abu Bakr al Baghdadi]. That was the biggest, maybe the biggest, one of the biggest ever, bigger than anything. That story disappeared so fast, gone, and that's OK. I didn't do it for the story. … If I were a Democrat, they'd be talking about that story for weeks.”
pageContext.analysis: There is simply no basis for this claim. Al Baghdadi's death received widespread coverage, comparable to the coverage of the death of Osama bin Laden.
